# Task 3: Saturday Lab — Metasploitable Setup and Exploitation

## Overview
This folder documents the Saturday session, which covered setting up a
Metasploitable 2 virtual machine, scanning it to identify vulnerable services,
and exploiting the vsftpd 2.3.4 backdoor using the Metasploit Framework to
gain a root shell on the target machine.

---

## Environment
| Component | Details |
|-----------|---------|
| Attacker | Kali Linux — 192.168.56.102 |
| Target | Metasploitable 2 — 192.168.56.101 |
| Network | VirtualBox Host-Only Adapter |
| Metasploit Version | v6.4.84-dev |
| Date | 8 May 2026 |

---

## Setup Process

### Step 1 — Download Metasploitable 2
Download from: https://sourceforge.net/projects/metasploitable/

### Step 2 — Extract the archive
Extract the ZIP file. You will find a `.vmdk` disk image inside.

### Step 3 — Create a new VM in VirtualBox
